  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2000-06-29", 
    "text": "Miranda Reaffirmation Act of 2000 - Repeals provisions of the Federal criminal code providing that: (1) a confession shall be admissible in any criminal prosecution brought by the United States or by the District of Columbia if it is given voluntarily; and (2) the trial judge, in determining the issue of voluntariness, shall take into consideration all circumstances surrounding the confession."
